title: From Beyond the Unknown (DC ) (1969-1973) #1 - #25 (Complete)
description:
From Wikipedia:

From Beyond the Unknown was the title of a science-fiction comic book series published by DC Comics. It ran for 25 issues from October 1969 to December 1973.

From Beyond the Unknown was an anthology series, whose tag-line promised to provide "Stories that Stagger the Imagination." The series reprinted stories from earlier DC Comics' anthologies, including Strange Adventures and Mystery in Space. Covers featured such imaginative settings as an alien auctioneer preparing to sell the earth, or an ape-man trying to conquer the world.

Writers

* Otto Binder
* John Broome
* Gardner Fox

Artists

* Neal Adams
* Murphy Anderson
* Carmine Infantino
* Gil Kane
* Joe Kubert
* Bob Oksner
* Mike Sekowsky

...and many more. I got this in a torrent myself "somewhere else" (don't recall) and have had some of the originals in my collection for years. I was quite happy to complete the collection. These are FUN comics, and make a nice sampler of DC's sometimes goofy-but-loveable science fiction comics of the 50's and 60's. A HUGE thanks to the original scanners and uploader.
